content.text: What is the stiffness matrix for this part of the groove structure?

The red circle highlights a groove entrance. Ensuring upward and downward movement, particularly normal to the table (aligned with the z-axis), requires higher stiffness in the z-direction while maintaining low stiffness in the other directions. This approach minimizes potential groove damage during manipulation.
